{"id":1629,"date":"2013-10-13T15:15:02","date_gmt":"2013-10-13T14:15:02","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/?page_id=1629"},"modified":"2015-12-07T00:02:18","modified_gmt":"2015-12-06T23:02:18","slug":"big-data-insights","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/consumer-data-insights\/big-data-insights\/","title":{"rendered":"Big Data &#038; Insights"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Geo Strategies specialises in the organisation and structuring of Big Data to help companies understand their customers.<\/span><b><\/b><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><b>Understanding your customer<\/b><\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>There i<a href=\"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/10\/Big-Data.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-1617 alignright\" alt=\"Big Data\" src=\"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/10\/Big-Data.jpg\" width=\"72\" height=\"62\" \/><\/a>s a huge difference between <a href=\"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/09\/Big-Data.pdf\"><strong>Big Data<\/strong><\/a>\u00c2\u00a0and the Right Data.<\/p>\n<p>Thanks to modern technology organisations have access to huge quantities of data about their customers.<\/p>\n<p>However, this is useless unless it is combined and filtered. What everybody requires is relevant, timely and actionable information about prospects and customers.<\/p>\n<p>There are four basic sources of data:<\/p>\n<p><strong>Transactional<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Sales data, basket analysis, product purchases, usage, payment behaviours<\/p>\n<p><strong>Demographic<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Lifestyle, life stage, age, gender, household income<\/p>\n<p><strong>Psychographic<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Attitudes, sentiments, peer reviews, needs, brand perceptions<\/p>\n<p><strong>Behavioural<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Search, sites used, e-mail clicks, content viewed<\/p>\n<p>In particular, behavioural data is beginning to swamp organisations with the ever-increasing use of social media.<\/p>\n<p>The holy grail for all organisations is the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/single-customer-view\/\">Single Customer View<\/a> (SCV). This is possible within e.g. a bank or insurance company where customers may have multiple accounts but, more typically, it is only possible to combine external data with internal data at a household or address level.<\/p>\n<p>Geo Strategies can assist in six areas:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>With <strong>demographic data<\/strong> based on\u00c2\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/consumer-data-insights\/segmentations\/mosaic-romania\/\">Mosaic<\/a> for Romania. This anonymised data covers every single household in Romania.<\/li>\n<li>With <strong>psychographic data<\/strong> based on <a href=\"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/consumer-data-insights\/segmentations\/lifestyle-data\/\">Lifestyle data <\/a>which includes information on shopping preferences, attitudes and similar.<\/li>\n<li>By<strong> cleansing and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/de-duplication\/\">de-duplicating<\/a><\/strong> contact data as the first step towards a SCV<\/li>\n<li>By <strong>standardising and \u00c2\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/data-quality-management\/geocoding\/\">geocoding<\/a><\/strong> addresses so that they can be located on a map<\/li>\n<li>With data collected as a result of using the <strong>Experian Cross Channel Marketing Platform<\/strong> (EECMP).<\/li>\n<li>By <strong>combining and filtering data<\/strong> using <a href=\"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/alteryx\/\">BI tools<\/a>.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>In all cases, these services can be provided as products or carried out in-house.<\/p>\n<p>See also &#8211;<\/p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/10\/Big-Data-for-Dummies.pdf\">Big Data for Dummies<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Geo Strategies specialises in the organisation and structuring of Big Data to help companies understand their customers. Understanding your customer &nbsp; There is a huge difference between Big Data\u00c2\u00a0and the Right Data. Thanks to modern technology organisations have access to huge quantities of data about their customers. However, this is useless unless it is combined [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":0,"parent":990,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","template":"","meta":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1629"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/4"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1629"}],"version-history":[{"count":25,"href":"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1629\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1767,"href":"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1629\/revisions\/1767"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/990"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.geo-strategies.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1629"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}